page.title: 01NE Corner Dalby Forest
page.content: Mainly area of coniferous forest planted by Forestry Commission dating back to early 1920's. A dissected plateau part of the tabular hills. Valleys mainly due to glacier action and flood water melt. Very popular with walkers & summer visitors. Many forest walks & trails. The Dalby Forest drive winds its way through the block. The older crops not being felled and replanted with conifers and sprinkling of broad leaved trees. The man made Staindale lake lies on east or block. Fome FC smallholdings & farms break up the area. Mainly sheep and store cattle with some arable crops in rotation. The SE corner abuts on Trousdale. A scenic drive from the A170 Scarborough - Pickering Road.
